01:09:58.350 --> 01:09:59.430
at the end of this class.

01:09:59.430 --> 01:10:01.770
But I'm telling you now
what the party line is,

01:10:01.770 --> 01:10:03.510
and what's in your textbook.

01:10:03.510 --> 01:10:05.850
What's in your textbook
and what the party line is

01:10:05.850 --> 01:10:09.090
is that when you use
historical amounts of data,

01:10:09.090 --> 01:10:12.730
those kind of crisis periods
are in there already.

01:10:12.730 --> 01:10:14.430
So if I estimate
the correlations,

01:10:14.430 --> 01:10:19.560
including October '87, including
March 2000, the bursting

01:10:19.560 --> 01:10:22.770
of the internet bubble,
August 1998, LTCM,

01:10:22.770 --> 01:10:25.960
if I include all of
those in my data,

01:10:25.960 --> 01:10:27.360
then it's captured in there.

01:10:27.360 --> 01:10:28.720
Right?

01:10:28.720 --> 01:10:30.530
It's not captured today.

01:10:30.530 --> 01:10:33.790
In other words, this point
here for General Dynamics

01:10:33.790 --> 01:10:36.490
doesn't reflect that
there's a crisis today.

01:10:36.490 --> 01:10:40.640
What it reflects is, on average,
over a long period of time--

01:10:40.640 --> 01:10:42.760
some of which includes crises--

01:10:42.760 --> 01:10:45.810
that's what the expected
return looks like.

01:10:45.810 --> 01:10:50.580
And so I've already incorporated
that into the parameters.

01:10:50.580 --> 01:10:53.310
And if it so happens that
today is a bad day for General

01:10:53.310 --> 01:10:55.620
Dynamics, that
shouldn't influence

01:10:55.620 --> 01:10:56.850
whether you buy it or not.

01:10:56.850 --> 01:10:58.558
Because what you should
be thinking about

01:10:58.558 --> 01:11:03.360
is over the next 15 or 20
years, how will my portfolio do.

01:11:03.360 --> 01:11:06.210
So that's another difference
in perspective from us

01:11:06.210 --> 01:11:07.890
versus Warren Buffett.

01:11:07.890 --> 01:11:10.290
Although actually, not
as much as you think.

01:11:10.290 --> 01:11:13.290
Warren Buffett typically takes
a long term perspective, right?

01:11:13.290 --> 01:11:15.042
His investment in Goldman Sachs?

01:11:15.042 --> 01:11:16.500
We all thought it
was a great deal.

01:11:16.500 --> 01:11:18.540
He's lost money in it
