01:11:39.450 --> 01:11:42.510
Because these kind of
parameters aren't made for day

01:11:42.510 --> 01:11:44.130
to day forecasting.

01:11:44.130 --> 01:11:45.930
Then you need to get
hedge fund models.

01:11:45.930 --> 01:11:48.380
And for that, you need
to take not only 433,

01:11:48.380 --> 01:11:50.130
but a number of other
courses, and courses

01:11:50.130 --> 01:11:51.210
that aren't even offered yet.

01:11:51.210 --> 01:11:53.070
Because frankly, if I
told you how to do it,

01:11:53.070 --> 01:11:53.945
I'd have to kill you.

01:11:53.945 --> 01:11:54.570
Right?

01:11:54.570 --> 01:11:56.850
Highly proprietary.

01:11:56.850 --> 01:11:59.370
But this is the
approach where we're not

01:11:59.370 --> 01:12:00.660
trying to forecast markets.

01:12:00.660 --> 01:12:02.460
And so I'm acknowledging
that you're

01:12:02.460 --> 01:12:04.470
right that there
are instabilities.

01:12:04.470 --> 01:12:06.720
But as long as I'm using a
long enough amount of data,

01:12:06.720 --> 01:12:07.590
that it's in there.

01:12:07.590 --> 01:12:10.550
It's captured in there,
in that set of parameters.

01:12:10.550 --> 01:12:11.610
OK?

01:12:11.610 --> 01:12:14.310
If it's not, if you know of
something that's not in here,

01:12:14.310 --> 01:12:17.250
obviously you can't expect this
to give you the right answer.

01:12:17.250 --> 01:12:20.580
And you have to adjust your
use of this technology,

01:12:20.580 --> 01:12:23.190
accordingly.

01:12:23.190 --> 01:12:24.650
Other questions?

01:12:24.650 --> 01:12:25.326
Yeah?

01:12:25.326 --> 01:12:29.404
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE]

01:12:29.404 --> 01:12:30.070
ANDREW LO: Yeah.

01:12:30.070 --> 01:12:45.080
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE]

01:12:45.080 --> 01:12:46.430
ANDREW LO: Yeah.

01:12:46.430 --> 01:12:47.230
That's right.

01:12:47.230 --> 01:12:47.760
Yeah.

01:12:47.760 --> 01:12:54.800
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE]

01:12:54.800 --> 01:12:56.660
ANDREW LO: Well,
